#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:1
msgid "Using Python"
msgstr "使用 Python"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:3
msgid ""
"VTK is available on [PyPI](https://pypi.org/) for Windows, macOS and Linux."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:4
msgid "pip install vtk\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:7
msgid ""
"or in a [virtual environment](https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html) "
"if you want to install the package only locally instead of system-wide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:0
msgid "Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:14
#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:23
msgid ""
"python -m venv ./env\n"
"source ./env/bin/activate\n"
"pip install vtk\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:0
msgid "macOS"
msgstr "macOS"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:0
msgid "Windows"
msgstr "Windows"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:31
msgid "Using `PowerShell`"
msgstr "使用 `PowerShell`"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:32
msgid ""
"python -m venv env\n"
".\\env\\Activate.ps1\n"
"pip install vtk\n"
msgstr ""
"python -m venv env\n"
".\\env\\Activate.ps1\n"
"pip install vtk\n"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:38
msgid "or using `cmd.exe`"
msgstr "或者使用 `cmd.exe`"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:39
msgid ""
"python -m venv env\n"
".\\env\\activate.bat\n"
"pip install vtk\n"
msgstr ""
"python -m venv env\n"
".\\env\\activate.bat\n"
"pip install vtk\n"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:47
msgid ""
"To verify the installation try to import vtk from an interactive python "
"environment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:49
msgid ""
">>> import vtk\n"
">>> print(vtk.__version__)\n"
"9.2.6\n"
msgstr ""
">>> import vtk\n"
">>> print(vtk.__version__)\n"
"9.2.6\n"

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:55
msgid ""
"That's it ! You may now try some of the [tutorials](https://kitware.github."
"io/vtk-examples/site/Python/#tutorial), [how to guides](https://kitware."
"github.io/vtk-examples/site/PythonHowTo) or [examples](https://kitware."
"github.io/vtk-examples/site/Python)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:60
msgid ""
"If you are looking for a higher-level interface to VTK in Python, you may "
"want to explore using [PyVista](https://docs.pyvista.org) as it exposes VTK "
"in a \"Pythonic\" manner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_python.md:64
msgid ""
"If you are running the script in a Linux/Windows machine without a display "
"or a GPU, VTK will automatically select an appropriate OpenGL render window "
"class. Please learn more about how you can influence the render window "
"selection process in [](/advanced/runtime_settings.md#opengl)"
msgstr ""
